										<footer class="article-contributor contributors">
									

<div class="block-contributor">
		

		<div class="block-contributor-content">
		<div class="block-contributor-bio small">
			<p><strong><span class="smallcaps">Ram Dass</span></strong> is the former Harvard professor turned psychedelic explorer turned spiritual teacher. He has done for religion what the Beatles did for music. In his books &mdash; <em>Be Here Now</em>, <em>The Only Dance There Is</em>, <em>Grist for the Mill</em>, <em>Journey of Awakening</em>, and <em>Miracle of Love</em> &mdash; Ram Dass translates Eastern ideas for Westerners and tells of his remarkable experiences with his guru, Neem Karoli Baba, or Maharaji, who died in 1973.</p><a href="/contributors/ram-dass" class="block-contributor-link link-alt small">More From This Contributor&nbsp;&#9656;</a>		</div>
	</div>
</div>

